.SH NAME
MediaQueryList.media \- MediaQueryList: media property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]media\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property of the
\f[CR]MediaQueryList\f[R] interface is a string representing a
serialized media query.
.SH VALUE
A string representing a serialized media query.
.SH EXAMPLES
This example runs the media query \f[CR](max\-width: 600px)\f[R] and
displays the value of the resulting \f[CR]MediaQueryList\f[R]\[cq]s
\f[CR]media\f[R] property in a \f[CR]<span>\f[R].
.SS JavaScript
.IP
.EX
\f[B]let\f[R] mql = window.matchMedia(\[dq](max\-width: 600px)\[dq]);

document.querySelector(\[dq].mq\-value\[dq]).innerText = mql.media;
.EE
.PP
The JavaScript code passes the media query to match into
\f[CR]matchMedia()\f[R] to compile it, then sets the
\f[CR]<span>\f[R]\[cq]s \f[CR]innerText\f[R] to the value of the
result\[cq]s \f[CR]media\f[R] property.
.SS HTML
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]span\f[R] class=\[dq]mq\-value\[dq]></\f[B]span\f[R]>
.EE
.PP
A simple \f[CR]<span>\f[R] to receive the output.
